words.def: A pointed tool without any sharp edges, used in weaving or knotwork to tighten and form up weaves or complex knots; used in sailing ships to open the strands of a rope before splicing. Compare marlinespike.
the cardinal number that is the sum of four and one
a loud harsh or strident noise
An uncertainty, possibility, condition, doubt etc.
a state in the Rocky Mountains
a unit of length equal to one twelfth of a foot
